article.headline: Ill.-Chicago 84, Cent. Michigan 62
article.story: CHICAGO (AP) -- Othyus Jeffers scored 24 points and grabbed nine rebounds, both game highs, to lead Illinois-Chicago to an 84-62 win over Central Michigan on Saturday. The Flames (11-17) led 29-24 at halftime, and used a 16-6 run midway through the second half to take control of the game. Later, Jeffers scored eight straight points to put the Flames ahead 80-54 with 3:39 left. Josh Mayo scored 16 points and dished out eight assists for UIC. T.J. Gray added 16 points, and Robert Bush chipped in 12. Marko Spica scored 18 points and hauled in eight rebounds to lead the Chippewas (10-15). The Flames out-shot Central Michigan 46.6 percent to 39.6 percent and scored 29 points off 22 Chippewa turnovers.
